1 = NonResponse(<30% reduction in HRSD scores and HRSD >15 for 2 consecutive visits and met the DSM-IV criteria for MDD for 2 consecutive visits during weeks 6, 8, 10, and 12) 2 = Partial Response(not meeting criteria for NonResponse or Remission) 3 = Remission(>60% reduction in HRSD scores and HRSD <8 for 2 consecutive visits and does not meet DSM-IV criteria for MDD for 2 consecutive visits during weeks 6, 8, 10, and 12)If the patient meets the criteria for NonResponse the patient will advance to the Randomization Phase (Phase II). If the patient has had a partial response, continue at the maximum tolerated dose of the current medication up to week 12 then advance to the Randomization Phase. If the patient meets the criteria for Remission at week 12, continue on current medications in Phase II with patient visits scheduled only once every 4 weeks.
